Notes.Text:
This update for ImageMagick fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2022-44267: Fixed a denial of service when parsing a PNG image (bsc#1207982).
- CVE-2022-44268: Fixed arbitrary file disclosure when parsing a PNG image (bsc#1207983).

Vulnerabilities.Description: ImageMagick 7.1.0-49 is vulnerable to Information Disclosure. When it parses a PNG image (e.g., for resize), the resulting image could have embedded the content of an arbitrary. file (if the magick binary has permissions to read it).
